  "ref_code": "ARCH-CORE-ASPIRE-APPHOST",
  "title": "Aspire AppHost & Infrastructure Design",
  "slug": "aspire-apphost",
  "category": "reference",
  "content": [
    "## 1. AppHost Resource Topology",
    "",
    "See diagram `DIAG-CORE-ASPIRE-TOPOLOGY` for the visual topology (mermaid c4_container).",
    "",
    "## 2. Dual-Mode Infrastructure Pattern",
    "",
    "Each infrastructure resource has two modes: **local containers** for development (via `RunAsContainer` / `RunAsEmulator`) and **Azure managed services** for deployment. A single definition in Program.cs serves both environments.",
    "",
    "### 2a. PostgreSQL",
    "",
    "```",
    "Local (dotnet run):",
    "  AddAzurePostgresFlexibleServer(\"dbserver\")",
    "    .RunAsContainer(c => c.WithDataVolume().WithPgAdmin())",
    "    .AddDatabase(\"actionsdb\", \"amps-actions\");",
    "",
    "Azure (azd up):",
    "  Azure PostgreSQL Flexible Server v17",
    "    SKU: Burstable Standard_B2s",
    "    Authentication: Entra ID only (password auth disabled)",
    "    Managed Identity: API gets PostgreSQL admin role assignment",
    "    Connection: ManagedIdentityCredential (no password in connection string)",
    "```",
    "",
    "**Actions-specific:** Single database `amps-actions` with `actions` schema for all domain entities. RLS policies on all tenant-scoped tables. A background role `amps_background` is used by background services (ledger verification, escalation checks) that need cross-tenant access.",
    "",
    "### 2b. Redis",
    "",
    "```",
    "Local (dotnet run):",
    "  AddAzureManagedRedis(\"redis\")",
    "    .RunAsContainer();",
    "",
    "Azure (azd up):",
    "  Azure Managed Redis (Enterprise-tier)",
    "    Active geo-replication, 99.99% SLA",
    "    Used for BFF session storage",
    "```",
    "",
    "**Actions-specific:** Redis stores BFF session data (access tokens, refresh tokens, user claims). The API itself does not use Redis directly — all caching is done at the BFF layer.",
    "",
    "### 2c. Azure Blob Storage",
    "",
    "```",
    "Local (dotnet run):",
    "  AddAzureStorage(\"storage\")",
    "    .RunAsEmulator(e => e.WithDataBindMount(\"../Azurite/Data\"))",
    "    .AddBlobs(\"blobs\");",
    "",
    "Azure (azd up):",
    "  Azure Storage Account",
    "    Blob containers for evidence file storage",
    "    Pre-signed URL pattern for uploads/downloads",
    "```",
    "",
    "**Actions-specific:** Evidence files (documents, images, reports) uploaded by users are stored in blob storage. The API generates pre-signed SAS URLs for direct browser-to-storage uploads, avoiding proxying large files through the API.",
    "",
    "---",
    "",
    "## 3. Connection String Strategy",
    "",
    "### How Connection Strings Flow",
    "",
    "```",
    "                    Aspire AppHost",
    "                         │",
    "          ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐",
    "          ▼              ▼              ▼",
    "  ConnectionStrings   ConnectionStrings  ConnectionStrings",
    "  __actionsdb         __redis           __blobs",
    "          │              │              │",
    "          ▼              ▼              ▼",
    "      API/BFF processes (environment variables)",
    "          │",
    "          ▼",
    "  configuration.GetConnectionString(\"actionsdb\")",
    "  configuration.GetConnectionString(\"redis\")",
    "  configuration.GetConnectionString(\"blobs\")",
    "```",
    "",
    "### Three Operating Modes",
    "",
    "| Mode | Connection Source | When Used |",
    "|------|-------------------|-----------|",
    "| **Aspire (primary)** | AppHost injects `ConnectionStrings__<name>` as env vars | `dotnet run --project Nxgn.Actions.AppHost` |",
    "| **Standalone (fallback)** | `appsettings.Development.json` hardcoded strings | `dotnet run --project Nxgn.Actions.Api` (no Aspire) |",
    "| **Azure (production)** | Aspire generates from Bicep outputs + managed identity | `azd up` / `azd deploy` |",
    "",
    "---",
    "",
    "## 4. Configuration Layering — appsettings",
    "",
    "### 4a. appsettings.json (base — production defaults, committed)",
    "",
    "```",
    "Logging levels (suppress noisy components)",
    "AllowedHosts",
    "ForwardedHeaders (TrustAllProxies: true, IngressOnlyConfirmed: true)",
    "RateLimiting (production limits: strict)",
    "VirusScan settings (enabled, service URL)",
    "Identity authority URL (from environment variable)",
    "```",
    "",
    "### 4b. appsettings.Development.json (dev overrides, committed)",
    "",
    "```",
    "Logging (more verbose)",
    "Cors:AllowedOrigins = [\"http://localhost:4200\"]",
    "RateLimiting (relaxed limits)",
    "ConnectionStrings (fallback for standalone mode — localhost)",
    "VirusScan:Enabled = false (no virus scanner locally)",
    "Identity:Authority = \"https://localhost:5001\" (local Identity)",
    "```",
    "",
    "### 4c. User Secrets (per-developer, NEVER committed)",
    "",
    "| Project | Secrets Stored |",
    "|---------|---------------|",
    "| **AppHost** | Container sizing parameters, npmrc for private npm registry |",
    "| **Api** | Identity authority URL override, API key validation endpoint |",
    "",
    "### 4d. Azure (production, NEVER committed)",
    "",
    "| Secret | Storage | Injection |",
    "|--------|---------|-----------|",
    "| PostgreSQL credentials | Managed Identity (no password) | Automatic via `EnrichAzureNpgsqlDbContext` |",
    "| Redis connection | Azure provisioning | Aspire injects via Bicep outputs |",
    "| Blob storage connection | Managed Identity | Aspire injects via Bicep outputs |",
    "| `.npmrc` (private npm registry) | GitHub Secrets → `npmrc` parameter | Docker build secret |",
    "",
    "---",
    "",
    "## 5. Azure Deployment Architecture",
    "",
    "### Resource Map",
    "",
    "```",
    "Resource Group: rg-nxgn-actions-{env}",
    "│",
    "├── Container App Environment",
    "│   ├── Azure Container Registry",
    "│   └── Log Analytics Workspace",
    "│",
    "├── actions-api (Container App)",
    "│   ├── User Assigned Managed Identity",
    "│   ├── PostgreSQL admin role assignment",
    "│   └── Storage Blob Data Contributor role",
    "│",
    "├── actions-bff (Container App)",
    "│   └── Redis connection via Aspire Bicep",
    "│",
    "├── actions-ui (Container App)",
    "│   └── Dockerfile: Node build → nginx:alpine",
    "│       └── .npmrc as Docker build secret",
    "│",
    "├── dbserver (PostgreSQL Flexible Server v17)",
    "│   ├── Burstable Standard_B2s",
    "│   ├── Entra ID auth only (password disabled)",
    "│   ├── Database: amps-actions",
    "│   └── Schema: actions (all domain entities)",
    "│",
    "├── redis (Azure Managed Redis — Enterprise)",
    "│   └── BFF session storage",
    "│",
    "└── storage (Azure Storage Account)",
    "    └── Blob container: evidence",
    "```",
    "",
    "### Managed Identity Flow (no passwords in production)",
    "",
    "```",
    "actions-api Container App",
    "    │",
    "    ├── Has: User Assigned Managed Identity",
    "    │",
    "    ├── PostgreSQL: MI has admin role → acquires Azure AD token",
    "    │   via EnrichAzureNpgsqlDbContext<ActionsDbContext>()",
    "    │",
    "    └── Blob Storage: MI has Storage Blob Data Contributor role",
    "        → generates user-delegation SAS tokens for evidence uploads",
    "```",
    "",
    "---",
    "",
    "## 6. AppHost Program.cs — Actual Design",
    "",
    "```csharp",
    "var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);",
    "",
    "var acaEnv = builder.AddAzureContainerAppEnvironment(\"aca-env\");",
    "",
    "// === PostgreSQL (dual-mode) ===",
    "var postgres = builder.AddAzurePostgresFlexibleServer(\"dbserver\")",
    "    .ConfigureInfrastructure(infra => {",
    "        var server = infra.GetProvisionableResources()",
    "            .OfType<PostgreSqlFlexibleServer>().Single();",
    "        server.Version = \"17\";",
    "        server.Sku = new { Tier = Burstable, Name = \"Standard_B2s\" };",
    "    })",
    "    .RunAsContainer(c => c.WithDataVolume().WithPgAdmin());",
    "var actionsDb = postgres.AddDatabase(\"actionsdb\", \"amps-actions\");",
    "",
    "// === Redis (dual-mode — Enterprise in Azure, container locally) ===",
    "var redis = builder.AddAzureManagedRedis(\"redis\").RunAsContainer();",
    "",
    "// === Blob Storage (dual-mode — Azure Storage in prod, Azurite locally) ===",
    "var storage = builder.AddAzureStorage(\"storage\")",
    "    .RunAsEmulator(e => e.WithDataBindMount(\"../Azurite/Data\"));",
    "var blobs = storage.AddBlobs(\"blobs\");",
    "",
    "// === Container sizing parameters (Azure only) ===",
    "var apiContainerCpu = builder.AddParameter(\"ApiContainerCpu\");",
    "var apiContainerMem = builder.AddParameter(\"ApiContainerMem\");",
    "var bffContainerCpu = builder.AddParameter(\"BffContainerCpu\");",
    "var bffContainerMem = builder.AddParameter(\"BffContainerMem\");",
    "",
    "// === API Service ===",
    "var api = builder.AddProject<Projects.Nxgn_Actions_Api>(\"actions-api\")",
    "    .WithReference(actionsDb).WaitFor(actionsDb)",
    "    .WithReference(blobs)",
    "    .WithExternalHttpEndpoints()",
    "    .PublishAsAzureContainerApp((infra, app) => { /* CPU/Memory */ });",
    "",
    "// === BFF (YARP proxy + session management) ===",
    "var bff = builder.AddProject<Projects.Nxgn_Actions_Web_Bff>(\"actions-bff\")",
    "    .WithReference(redis).WaitFor(redis)",
    "    .WithReference(api).WaitFor(api)",
    "    .WithExternalHttpEndpoints()",
    "    .PublishAsAzureContainerApp((infra, app) => { /* CPU/Memory */ });",
    "",
    "// === Angular SPA ===",
    "var npmrc = builder.AddParameter(\"npmrc\", secret: true);",
    "builder.AddJavaScriptApp(\"actions-ui\", \"../Nxgn.Actions.Web.Ui\")",
    "    .WithReference(bff).WaitFor(bff)",
    "    .WithHttpEndpoint(port: 4200, env: \"PORT\")",
    "    .WithExternalHttpEndpoints()",
    "    .PublishAsDockerFile(x => x.WithBuildSecret(\"npmrc\", npmrc));",
    "",
    "builder.Build().Run();",
    "```",
    "",
    "---",
    "",
    "## 7. Service Architecture",
    "",
    "```",
    "Browser ──cookie──> actions-bff ──Bearer JWT──> actions-api ──> PostgreSQL",
    "                        │                           │              (actionsdb)",
    "                        │                           │",
    "                        ▼                           ▼",
    "                      Redis                    Blob Storage",
    "                  (sessions)              (evidence files)",
    "                                                │",
    "                                                ▼",
    "                                          Identity API",
    "                                    (API key validation,",
    "                                     JWKS for JWT verify)",
    "",
    "M2M Service ──X-API-Key──> actions-api ──POST /api/v1/apikeys/validate──> Identity API",
    "```",
    "",
    "### Key Integration Points",
    "",
    "| Integration | Protocol | Purpose |",
    "|-------------|----------|---------|",
    "| BFF → Identity | OpenID Connect | User authentication (authorize, token, logout) |",
    "| API → Identity | HTTPS (JWKS) | Offline JWT validation via cached signing keys |",
    "| API → Identity | HTTPS (POST) | Online API key validation (`/api/v1/apikeys/validate`) |",
    "| API → Blob Storage | Azure SDK | Generate pre-signed SAS URLs for evidence uploads |",
    "| BFF → API | YARP reverse proxy | Forward authenticated requests with Bearer token |",
    "| BFF → Redis | StackExchange.Redis | Store/retrieve session data (tokens, claims) |"
  ],
